Sanity run:
Copy code
Bash
python3 pmos-port-assist.py samples/boot.log --safe --timeline --json --project /tmp/pmos_test
Compare:
Copy code
Bash
python3 pmos-port-assist.py samples/new.log --safe --compare samples/old.log --project /tmp/pmos_test
Pulse (stdin):
Copy code
Bash
cat samples/boot.log | python3 pmos-port-assist.py - --pulse
Pulse (file tail):
Copy code
Bash
python3 pmos-port-assist.py samples/boot.log --pulse
Watchdog checks
Dry-ish run on a connected device:
Copy code
Bash
PROJECT=/tmp/wd_test MAX_REBOOTS=2 TIMEOUT_MIN=1 ./pmos-watchdog.sh
Pulse integration:
Copy code
Bash
PROJECT=/tmp/wd_test MAX_REBOOTS=2 TIMEOUT_MIN=1 PULSE=1 ./pmos-watchdog.sh
Submitting a PR
Include:
What problem it solves (1–3 sentences)
Why it’s safe (backward compatible, defaults unchanged)
How you tested (commands + result summary)
If redaction behavior changes: list what new patterns are covered
Style notes
Python
Prefer small pure helpers; avoid big rewrites.
No heavy external libraries.
Keep types and dataclasses simple.
Bash
Quote variables.
Avoid parsing human text when structured outputs exis
